=Description=

"Temporary use is a practice where each empty building becomes an opportunity to develop new approaches to city making. [[Temporary Use Platforms]] turn empty spaces into resources to respond to urban crisis (housing, lack of affordable spaces) as well as create laboratories where occupants develop proofs of concepts in a broad range of fields such as horizontal democracy, tactical architecture, social economy, active education, urban food production, soft mobility, green energy, recycling, etc."
(https://www.stuncamp.org/about)

